</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
There are also a pair of summits named Pollux and Castor in Yellowstone National Park in Wyoming, USA. Located in the Absaroka Range, Pollux is 3,373 m, 65 m higher than its twin.</PARAGRAPH>
